threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3332 drop/water damage
threads.message:
"PpBUS_G3H NA"
What means NA???

"PP5V_S5 5.008"
That means you have some voltage on PPBUS_G3H...

Is there light on MagSafe?
Post SMC_ADAPTER_EN, PM_BATLOW_L and PM_SLP_SUS_L at least.

BTW, why did you bother measuring voltages on CPU and DDR suplies, when 5V_S3 is missing?

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3332 drop/water damage
threads.message: PPDCIN at 14.5V also suggests you are using a 45W charger. An 85W one will be 20V.

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3332 drop/water damage
threads.message: Yes i am, im currently using my personal charger which is from an a1466, I thought it would still boot but would crash under load?

threads.title: [SOLVED]820-3332 drop/water damage
threads.message: Only use an 85W charger for testing. 15" machines will not power on from anything else.
